Iran blocks use of the Google search engine, as it prepares to switch its citizens to a domestic internet network. (Reuters)Diplomatic tensions arise over Wednesday's "hit squad" Annecy murders. French investigators may or may not question Saad al-Hilli's colleagues at Surrey Satellite Technology Ltd, or SSTL, near Guildford. A British security source suggests as motive "state-sponsored assassination, rather than a family dispute". (The Independent) (Het Laatste Nieuws) (The Week)